abstract: Seven large health insurance carriers, following UnitedHealth/Oxford's lead, drop their objections to the public disclosure of their filings with New York State in support of rate increases; together, the eight insurers have 90 percent of the market of small group and individual insurance plans in the state.
snippet: After UnitedHealth/Oxford dropped its opposition recently, additional health insurance carriers have dropped their objections to the public disclosure of their filings with New York State.
lead_paragraph: After UnitedHealth/Oxford dropped its opposition recently, additional health insurance carriers have dropped their objections to the public disclosure of their filings with New York State.

headline.main: 7 More Insurers End Objections on Rate Filings
